---
description: Auto-triggers workers-events skill when event types, queues, or workers are created or modified.
globs: src/domains/**/events/**/*.ts, src/domains/**/queues/**/*.ts, src/domains/**/workers/**/*.ts, src/infrastructure/queue/**/*.ts, src/core/events/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

When any matching file is created or modified, read and follow the workers-events skill:
- Skill file: `.cursor/skills/workers-events/SKILL.md`
- Verify event types are properly defined and registered
- Ensure queues follow the BullMQ conventions (connection, job types, enqueue helpers)
- Validate workers have proper error handling, retries, and graceful shutdown
- Check that `infrastructure/queue/bootstrap.ts` registers all workers
